  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Version Information\r\n\r\n* vyper Version (output of `vyper --version`): 0.3.7+commit.6020b8b\r\n* OS: win\r\n* Python Version (output of `python --version`): `3.9.2`\r\n\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\n\r\nSince Vyper version `0.3.7` I can declare `immutable` and `constant` variables as `public`. If I now try to implement the following, the Vyper compiler will throw:\r\n\r\n```vy\r\nfrom vyper.interfaces import ERC20Detailed\r\nimplements: ERC20Detailed\r\n\r\n\r\ndecimals: public(constant(uint8)) = 18\r\nname: public(immutable(String[25]))\r\nsymbol: public(immutable(String[5]))\r\n```\r\n\r\nError message: `vyper.exceptions.InterfaceViolation: Contract does not implement all interface functions or events: decimals, name, symbol`.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\nAllow the usage of `public` `constant` & `immutable` variables for interface `view` functions.\r\n",
